&GLOBAL

  ! the project name is made part of most output files... useful to keep order 

  PRINT_LEVEL medium

  PROJECT ADP_SP_CALC1

  RUN_TYPE ENERGY_FORCE 
  

&END GLOBAL




&FORCE_EVAL

  METHOD QS

  !STRESS_TENSOR ANALYTICAL

  &PRINT

    &FORCES ON

    &END FORCES

  &END PRINT

  

  &SUBSYS

      &CELL 

        ABC [angstrom] 20.0 20.0 20.0


      &END CELL

      &TOPOLOGY

COORD_FILE_NAME output_993.xyz
        COORD_FILE_FORMAT XYZ

      &END


      &KIND H                              

        BASIS_SET DZVP-GTH       

        POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q1             

      &END KIND

      &KIND C

        BASIS_SET DZVP-GTH

        POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q4

      &END KIND

      &KIND N

        BASIS_SET DZVP-GTH

        POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q5

      &END KIND

      &KIND O

        BASIS_SET DZVP-GTH

        POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6

      &END KIND

    &END SUBSYS

  
  &DFT

    ! basis sets and pseudopotential files can be found in cp2k/data

    BASIS_SET_FILE_NAME HFX_BASIS

    POTENTIAL_FILE_NAME GTH_POTENTIALS     

    PLUS_U_METHOD MULLIKEN

    UKS .TRUE.       





    &MGRID


      REL_CUTOFF 60

      NGRIDS 5

      CUTOFF 800   

    &END MGRID



    &QS

       EPS_DEFAULT 1.0E-13    

    &END QS

    

    &XC



      &VDW_POTENTIAL

         POTENTIAL_TYPE PAIR_POTENTIAL 

         &PAIR_POTENTIAL

         REFERENCE_FUNCTIONAL PBE

            PARAMETER_FILE_NAME dftd3.dat

            TYPE DFTD3            

            

         &END PAIR_POTENTIAL

      &END VDW_POTENTIAL

      

      ! use a PBE functional 

      &XC_FUNCTIONAL PBE

      &END XC_FUNCTIONAL     

    &END XC

    &SCF     

    

      EPS_SCF 1.0E-6 ! accuracy of the SCF procedure typically 1.0E-6 - 1.0E-7                       

      MAX_SCF 50

      SCF_GUESS RESTART ! can be used to RESTART an interrupted calculation

      

      &OUTER_SCF ! repeat the inner SCF cycle 10 times

        

        EPS_SCF 1.0E-6 ! must match the above

        MAX_SCF 15

      &END OUTER_SCF

      

      &OT

      

        ENERGY_GAP 0.1

        PRECONDITIONER FULL_SINGLE_INVERSE

        MINIMIZER CG

        ! an accurate preconditioner suitable also for larger systems

        ! the most robust choice (DIIS might sometimes be faster, but not as stable).

      

      &END OT

    &END SCF

   &END DFT

 &END FORCE_EVAL

 





































    









